summary: Question about succesfully combining lifting and running. (or any other long-distance cardio form) via /r/Fitness
title: Question about succesfully combining lifting and running. (or any other long-distance cardio form) via /r/Fitness
body:
I have been lifting for two years now, mainly focussing on the compound lifts and getting stronger. (and obviously the aesthetic gains are nice)

A friend of mine asked me to join his goal of running a 21k. And I, because I want to motivate him (and like a new challenge). Would like to join him.

Now my question is since I dont want to lose strenght or size (I’m not that big 1.98 meter 100kg BW ~12-14% fat%) How do I do this? Just compensate the burned calories by eating more and keep lifting?

Would love some tips!



Submitted January 15, 2019 at 03:26AM by Iibertas
via reddit http://bit.ly/2SW7yEa

summary: Gym Adventures #1
title: Gym Adventures #1
body:
• the elliptical hurts my knees real bad
  • I need new sports bras (the girls may be small but they need a tight hug when jogging)
  • cycling is probably the easiest thing I did
  • lunges, fine. leg lifts with lunges, nearly fall over
  • hip raises (I giggle every time)
  • somewhere on another planet or universe is a Chey that can do pushups…earth Chey has much trouble
  • saunas make me lose my voice
  • I have strengthened my thought that showers are pure heaven.

blog.name: yaratriestobehealthy
blog.title: YARA
blog.description: kinda like a mood board but for health and fitness

body:
using this app to help me track my weight. what im doing exactly to lose weight is:


Intermittent fasting-

i allowed my self an eating window from 12pm-8pm anything before or after this will just be liquid fasting, for example this morning i made 24oz of peppermint tea for me to drink. i will also drink water and maybe even some sugar free gum or mints.


To complement the intermittent fasting im eating between 1200-1500 calories when i do eat. the only acceptions to this will be parties/events that i dont host. Even still i will maintain smaller portions and not eat as much


Im also cutting out foods from my diet such as diary, eggs, seafood, etc. So by the end of the year I will be fully vegan


Fitness-

For the first two months I will not be focusing on exercising too much. I want to really ground myself in my “diet” and I want to allow intermittent fasting time to feel more natural to me before I try to busy myself. I also will he recovering from my breast reduction all of february and maybe even some of march so I will have to remain inactive to allow myself to heal properly and without any complications.


Once I am healed however I will be starting off with a moderate yoga practice atleast 4-5 times a week for about a month. After this I will engage in more intense yoga practices and then take up some form of cardio. Im thinking biking, hiking, dancing, or anything else I may enjoy.


Im really anxious about going to a proper gym so hopefully by that time i would have lost a significant bit of weight and i wont have to worry about it too much.


Anyways so this is my current plan, im trying to remain action oriented in regards to making goals, however last night when I weighed myself I was 214 and this morning I was 209 so im super stocked about that. 1200-1500 calories I can easily manage but I am worried about what my mother will think.


Good luck girlies🎊
